data.title: Cheryl Facts & X-Factor Number Plates
data.meta_description: Happy Birthday Cheryl! We've listed some fun Cheryl facts on our blog and a selection of our X Number Plates which have the X-Factor, the perfect Birthday gift!
data.text:
From Cheryl Tweedy, to Cheryl Cole and now Cheryl Fernandez-Versini, Newcastle born Cheryl has certainly grabbed the hearts of the public throughout her career. She first found fame in 2002 when she joined Girls Aloud as part of the show Popstars: The Rivals. After the band achieved huge succes, she then went on to have an equally successful solo career, and of course she is also a very popular judge on The X Factor. She’s well known as a style icon and her style certainly starts trends.

Fascinating Facts about Cheryl Fernandez-Versini

Did you know…

Cheryl was in a British Gas advert in 1990, her brother Gary also starred in the advertisement.

She won a ‘bonniest baby’ contest run by Boots.

Cheryl has won the accolade of Sexiest Woman in the World twice.

She married Jean-Bernard Fernandez-Versini after dating him for just three months.

She climbed Mount Kilimanjaro to raise money for charity.
